column4:
Thank you for completing our questionnaire!

1. Your chances of carrying a BRCA mutation are very low.

2. Your chances of developing breast or ovarian cancer are average not increased.
"Average" risk means about 1 in 10 chance of getting breast cancer and about 1 in 100 chance of getting ovarian cancer.

column4:
Thank you for completing our questionnaire!

To assess your chances of carrying a BRCA mutation we need more information. Please see the summary on the next page that shows your answers and the information you were unable to provide.

Once you gather that additional information or if you cannot do so we recommend that you talk with a PAMC genetic counseling professional. Please call for that appointment: 650-555-1212.

The information you enter in this questionnaire is kept confidential. It is stored securely only inside our internal network. It will not be visible to unauthorized individuals or shared on the internet.

column4:
Thank you for completing our questionnaire!

Based on your answers we estimate that you may have a higher than average chance of carrying a BRCA mutation.To evaluate this more completely we recommend that you talk with a PAMC genetic counselor.Please enter your phone number below. We will attempt to contact you within one week.

This questionnaire asks questions about your health and your family's health history. Your answers will help decide whether you might benefit from tests to check for certain gene mutations (especially BRCA) that increase risk of certain cancers.

If you have already had such tests this questionnaire is not for you.

If you don't know the answers to the questions below please try to collect that information and then talk with your doctor.

To start the questionnaire please click the "Next" button. To learn more about any terms highlighted in blue simply tap them.
